<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="646" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thiébaut</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of France in the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-27"><hi rend="italic">April 27,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Adee</hi>: Referring to our conversation of
                            day before yesterday, I have the honor to transmit to you herewith for
                            your information copy of a telegram which the ambassador has received
                            from the agent of the steamer <hi rend="italic">Buena Ventura</hi>,
                            recently captured by the Federal squadron in the Gulf of Mexico: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p rend="right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Liverpool</hi>, <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1898</hi>.</p>
                                <p>Not being able to communicate with our <hi rend="italic">Buena
                                        Ventura</hi>, notwithstanding all efforts made, we beg you
                                    to be pleased to indicate to us in what way we can do so.
                                    Families anxious.</p>
                                <p rend="right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Larranaga.</hi></p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>The ambassador would be especially obliged to you if you could enable him
                            to answer this telegram. News of the crew of this vessel might doubtless
                            be obtained either from the Department of the Navy or the Treasury.</p>
                        <p>Be pleased to accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thiébaut.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>